messages.msgSnippet: ... Thanks for the support, and the laugh.  This was great. Now that I ve confessed to being kind of religious, I hope nobody s offended at this next thing.
messages.messageBody:
3/4/03 22:56:

> To end on a humorous note... once I was at a home birth meeting,
> expecting baby#4, and another pregnant lady who was a pagan also
> expecting her 4th child told me that her friends were teasing her
> that if she had any more babies, people would start to think she was
> a Christian! I couldn't stop laughing...

Thanks for the support, and the laugh. This was great.

Now that I've confessed to being kind of religious, I hope nobody's offended
at this next thing. (If you offend easily, stop reading now.) But this was
funny enough to need sharing. I drove past a Thai restaurant this past week
named.....Phuket

I don't know how that's supposed to be pronounced, but I know what I read it
as! I called my husband who about died laughing, and says we must go eat
there, and take photos, too!

brenda
